Merge pull request #10 from nickygerritsen/master

Add support for RSA-SHA1 signatures
Use HMAC-SHA1 as default
Add support for RSA-SHA1 signatures

Make src/src.pro target.path portable.

Instead of hardcoding the target path to /lib, use qmake's variables
for the targetpath.

Merge pull request #7 from iflatness/master

Allow for HEAD and DELETE requests
allow for head and delete requests

Merge pull request #6 from smartboyhw/master

Remove 64-bit multiarch implementation.

Remove 64-bit multiarch implementation.

Multiarch should not have been implemented in this way. Removing it.
Removed debian/ folder to prepare for Ubuntu deployment.

Merge pull request #5 from 0xd34df00d/master

Support opening auth page via a custom signal.

Support opening auth page via a custom signal.

QDesktopServices isn't always the perfect variant.

Merge pull request #2 from obenschaink/master

Replaced tab indentation with spaces.

Updates to recent patches to correct indentation to match
the style of the project (spaces instead of tabs).

Merge pull request #1 from obenschaink/master

Updates for handling requestTimedOut signal, multiple requests in flight and other improvements.

Added build instructions for Windows.

Additional documentation on error handling for requestReady().

Added documentation for several methods and signals.

Added CONTRIBUTORS section at the suggestion of Johan Paul.
Updated the comment for setTimeout()
Use QApplication instead of QCoreApplication with Qt5.

Fixed issue where the same nonce could potentially be used for
two separate requests if they were created within the same time in ms.
Set d->currentRequestType to the requestType of the request being processed.
Changed link flags for unit tests.
Use console config and modified link flags for windows builds.
Install into QT_INSTALL_PREFIX by default for windows builds.

Search for includes and headers in Qt default locations.
Changed link flags for windows.

Added requestTimeout() slot to handle requestTimedout() signals emitted from a KQOAuthRequest.

Use requestMap to map QNetworkReplies to KQOAuthRequest.  This is used in timeout to initiate
an abort() on the QNetworkReply.

Use requestMap to map QNetworkReplies in the slots that are connected to QNetworkReply finished() signals.
This allows the timeout and error handling code to run correctly if multiple KQOAuthRequest are active
at the same time.
Added requestMap to keep track of the mapping of KQOAuthRequests and QNetworkReplies.

Moved timeout() signal connect from requestTimerStart() to constructor.
This is to prevent a request used multiples times from accumulating multiple connections to the timeout() signal.
